\":\"[censored]\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"url\":\"http://baltctf.ru/\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":23},\"public_votable\":false}}'),(39,29,'HITB CTF Amsterdam 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/hitb.png\",\"id\":14,\"participants\":1,\"weight\":40,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"HITB CTF Amsterdam 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/14/\",\"location\":\"Amsterdam, Netherlands\",\"onsite\":true,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"Eindbazen\",\"id\":322}],\"format_id\":2,\"duration\":{\"hours\":7,\"days\":1},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"https://conference.hitb.org/hitbsecconf2017ams/capture-the-flag/\",\"ctf_id\":29,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-05-25T17:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-05-24T10:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"Capture the Flag – Bank0verflow will for the VERY FIRST TIME featuring a collaborative effort between the HITB.nl CTF Crew and OWASP.nl.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt will also be the first time HITB.nl is organising an Attack & Defense game, it will be similar to the CTF in HitbSecConf 2010 in Malaysia. Teams of 3 will have a set of daemons, services and web applications running on their machines and they need to exploit rival teams’ to get their flags. Submit the flag to obtain offensive points. Keep your daemons up and running to obtain defensive points.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor this game, every team will own a bank and will start with the same amount of money in the bank. Teams need to acquire spies to infiltrate rival banks to score offensive points. To obtain defensive points teams just need to keep their utilities up.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf a team reaches 0 euro before the game ends, the team is considered disqualified.\\r\\n\\r\\nWHAT TO BRING\\r\\n\\r\\n- Laptops\\r\\n- A network switch\\r\\n- Network cables\\r\\n- Extra power sockets.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe game will run through out the 2 days of the conference, starting from 10am – 5pm each day. Each team is limited to a maximum of 3 people. At the end of the day there can only be the top 3 winners.\\r\\nRULES\\r\\n\\r\\n- No flooding and/or DoS attack. Players will be penalized by disqualification, points deduction or time penalty.\\r\\n- No harassment of other opponents.\\r\\n- All participants must obey PIT STOP calls. PIT STOP calls are rest intervals where all players must leave the game area to facilitate for the CtF judges to update the score, and/or do maintenance work etc.\"}}'),(40,13,'PHD CTF Finals 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"The challenge is conducted according to the CTF (Capture the Flag) game rules. Several teams are to defend their own networks and attack the networks of other teams for a specified period of time. The aim of the contestants is detecting vulnerabilities in the systems of other competing teams and obtaining sensitive information (flags), and at the same time detecting and fixing vulnerabilities in their own systems.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe key feature of Positive Hack Days CTF is its closeness to real-life conditions. All the vulnerabilities are not fictional, but indeed occur on contemporary information systems. Moreover, the format of PHDays CTF is really wide due to the game environment’s saturation with unique elements (such as capturing and keeping control of the systems according to the King of the Hill principles, the option of solving game problems blindly — i.e. attacking systems without any access to them, etc.). CTF contestants will try themselves in real struggle and get a chance to develop their own information protection solutions.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo add special appeal to the contest, the game infrastructure is prepared and changed according to the story lines which are unique for each contest within PHDays CTF. Such conditions create a remarkable ambience and make the Positive Hack Days CTF contest to stand out against the background of other similar contests. \",\"ctf_id\":13,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-05-31T18:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-05-30T12:00:00+00:00\",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":2,\"duration\":{\"hours\":6,\"days\":1},\"url\":\"http://phdays.com/\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Moscow, Russia\",\"title\":\"PHD CTF Finals 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/11/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"weight\":60,\"participants\":3,\"id\":11,\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(41,1,'DEF CON CTF Qualifier 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/2/\",\"title\":\"DEF CON CTF Qualifier 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"Defense Diutinus Technologies Corp (ddtek) is pleased to announce the round of qualification for DEFON 20 CTF... DEFCON XX, it\'s two-thirds sheepornographic!\\r\\n\\r\\nIn case you have been under a rock, DEFCON 20 is poised to be the largest it has ever been, thousands and thousands of hackers, high end entertainment and non-stop action to rival m3rc\'s in romps New Zealand\'s sheep country.\\r\\n\\r\\nSo get your 50 gal. discount lube handy (use coupon code DDTEKNEEDZLUBEZ) and get ready to be pwned...the no-holds-barred competition for these coveted spots will be held over 48 non-stop hours 1-3 June (US time zones).\\r\\n\\r\\nThe qualification round will require teams to demonstrate the superiority of cyber, security, and hacking across a vast realm of security knowledge, practice and CISSP DRE exam prep questions.\\r\\n\\r\\nDT asked DDT to grow the CTF. So we have. We are pre-qualifying winners of other CTFs around the globe to bring a smackdown of epic proportions this August.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs always, last year\'s champion, the Euopean Nopsled Team, is granted automatic entry. There are so many CTFs on the circuit these days, we seek to incorporate only the best of the best.\\r\\n\\r\\nSo, random, wandering sheep have selected the following CTFs using a scientifically proven \\\"pin the tail on the m3rc\\\" (role reversal--who knew?) method.\\r\\n\\r\\nLast year the iCTF and Codegate winners demonstrated that winners of these CTFs were worthy of returning, additionally we invite victors from NCCDC, HitB, PhDays, nuit du hack, RuCTFE, and Defcon 19 oCTF.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe winners of said competitions have reserved seats at this years show.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhile DEFCON refuses to sell-out to corporate sponsorship, DT is personally covering two rooms per team at the majestic RIO hotel Thursday-Sunday for each team.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn honor of DC XX we\'re upping the number of tables in Vegas to 20 total. Yes, when the dust clears the _20_ best will be invited to join us this summer in sin city for the annual DEFCON deathmatch. It wouldn\'t be fair to reduce the number of spots available to the public at large, so 10 teams will qualify in open quals this June.\\r\\n\\r\\nReg is at ddtek.biz. Only those that pre-register for quals are permitted entry. Each individual should register. The first member of each team to register will receive a team code to privately share with other mates as they register. Just go to the dam site and register. It\'s not hard (registration that is), and lusers that can\'t bother themselves to register in the next eight weeks will be required to wear sheep hatz to Defcon (http://bit.ly/HCIQQy). Consider this your first challenge, those that successfully register will receive 5 schrute bucks (Schrute buck to bitcoin to sheepantler to qualpoint conversion scale will be available at a later date).\\r\\n\\r\\nRegistration site: https://www.ddtek.biz/reg/dc20_reg.jsp\\r\\nRegistration opens: 01 Apr 2012 00:00:00 UTC\\r\\nRegistration ends: 01 Jun 2012 00:00:00 UTC \\r\\n\\r\\nhttps://www.defcon.org/html/defcon-20/dc-20-ctf.html\\r\\nhttps://forum.defcon.org/showthread.php?t=12796\\r\\n\\r\\nFor those mathy types, you\'ll notice that one seat is not accounted for, stay tuned for a surprise announcement during quals weekend.\\r\\n\\r\\nMore infoz will follow via your registered email address.\\r\\n\\r\\nVulc@n\\r\\nDifensiva Senior Engineer, GIAC-OFFENSIVE\\r\\nDiuntinus Defense Technologies, plc., Co., Gmbh., Inc.\",\"finish\":\"2012-06-04T00:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-06-02T00:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":1,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://ddtek.biz/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[],\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":100,\"participants\":2,\"id\":2}}'),(42,25,'SECUINSIDE CTF Quals 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"url\":\"http://ctf.secuinside.com/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":25,\"finish\":\"2012-06-11T02:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-06-09T02:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"SECUINSIDE CTF Quals 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/25/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"id\":25,\"participants\":18,\"weight\":70,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(43,16,'Nuit du Hack CTF Finals 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":34,\"participants\":5,\"weight\":20,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"Nuit du Hack CTF Finals 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/34/\",\"location\":\"France, Paris\",\"onsite\":true,\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":2,\"public_votable\":false,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":9},\"url\":\"http://nuitduhack.com/\",\"ctf_id\":16,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-06-24T15:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-06-23T06:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"\"}}'),(44,34,'SECUINSIDE CTF Finals 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":35,\"participants\":2,\"weight\":60,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":0},\"url\":\"http://secuinside.com/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":32,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-07-10T06:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2012-07-11T06:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"SECUINSIDE CTF Finals 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/35/\",\"location\":\"Seul, Republic of Korea\",\"onsite\":true}}'),(45,2,'DEF CON CTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/dc20-logo_smsq.png\",\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"id\":26,\"participants\":10,\"weight\":80,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/26/\",\"title\":\"DEF CON CTF 2012\",\"location\":\"Las Vegas, NV, USA\",\"onsite\":true,\"format_id\":2,\"public_votable\":false,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":4},\"url\":\"http://ddtek.biz/\",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Prequalified\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-07-29T10:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-07-27T06:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":2,\"description\":\"Binjitsu IV by ddtek\"}}'),(46,33,'InCTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-08-19T14:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-08-17T06:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":31,\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":8},\"url\":\"http://portal.inctf.in/\",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"description\":\"1st International Conference on Security of Internet of Things - August 17 to 19 2012, Kerala, India.\\r\\nIndian students only.\\r\\n\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/33/\",\"title\":\"InCTF 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"India, Kerala\",\"participants\":2,\"id\":33,\"weight\":0,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\"}}'),(47,37,'BaltCTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Hack quest\",\"weight\":20,\"participants\":5,\"id\":41,\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Kaliningrad, Russia\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/41/\",\"title\":\"BaltCTF 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"\",\"finish\":\"2012-08-26T14:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-08-26T06:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":36,\"duration\":{\"hours\":8,\"days\":0},\"format_id\":3,\"url\":\"http://www.baltctf.ru/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":558,\"name\":\"[censored]\"}]}}'),(48,36,'DerbyCon 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Hack quest\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":40,\"participants\":1,\"weight\":0,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"DerbyCon 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/40/\",\"location\":\"Louisville, KY, USA\",\"onsite\":true,\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":0},\"format_id\":3,\"url\":\"https://www.derbycon.com/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":35,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-09-27T09:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2012-09-28T09:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"The capture the flag event will start on Friday at 1:00PM and will run until 1:00PM on Sunday. This year, there will be a dedicated capture the flag room and able to perform activities via wireless as well. The CTF is traditional in the sense you find exposures and vulnerabilities and need to get the hash off the target or exposure. A tracking system will be used to track realtime points.\\r\\n\\r\\nPrizes will be awarded to first, second, and third place winners.\\r\\n\\r\\nFirst place: iPad 3 – 64GB 4G LTE (Wireless) Model\\r\\nSecond place: Pwnplug Elite from Pwnie Express\\r\\nThird place: $200 prepaid mastercard\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease note that there are no qualifiers for the CTF, it will start Friday when the conference starts and end early on Sunday\"}}'),(49,18,'CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"CSAW CTF Organizers\",\"id\":2488}],\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"url\":\"https://ctf.csaw.io/\",\"ctf_id\":18,\"start\":\"2012-09-28T14:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-09-30T14:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"CSAW CTF is a entry-level CTF, designed for undergraduate students who are trying to break into security. Challenges are specifically designed to point students in directions that will help them understand fundamental concepts and develop practical skills. Our sponsors are big players in the security field, who are serious about hiring the right people with the right skills. Our judges are world-renowned experts in the security field, who are dedicated to making sure that our challenges are designed to test these skills.\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/42/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"id\":42,\"participants\":39,\"weight\":40,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(50,32,'HitbSecConf CTF (Kuala Lumpur) 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"weight\":30,\"id\":39,\"participants\":5,\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"\",\"description\":\"OVERVIEW\\r\\nTo celebrate the 10th year anniversary of HITBSecConf, the CTF Overlords and CTF Crews 1.0, 2.0 and the all-new 3.0 will be coming together to work on a 32 HOUR NON STOP CAPTURE THE FLAG COMPETITION which we’re calling CTF Weapons of Mass Destruction – Fallout Apocalypse!\\r\\nIn our previous CTF Weapons of Mass Destruction, Teams had a set of daemons / services running on their machines and they had to exploit rival teams’ daemons to steal their flags. Submit the flags to obtain offensive points and also unlock nuclear weapons that can be launched against rival teams. For defensive points, all the team had to do was to keep their daemons up and running.\\r\\nFallout Apocalypse will require each team to manage a nuclear power plant and protect their daemons, which represents the reactor’s cores, from attacks while at the same time launch attacks against rival teams’ nuclear reactor. Weaponized SCADA exploits can be used to cause monetary damage towards rival teams. Fallout Apocalypse will also feature a spanking new black market where teams may trade exploits and also purchase countermeasures.\\r\\nDETAILED EXPLANATION\\r\\nEach team will start with an equal amount of money which represents their points. More money can be obtained periodically by making sure daemons are all up and running during a flag check initiated by the score server. Money can also be obtained by achieving “Break through Points”, which will be awarded to the first team who manages to solve a daemon, or in other words, be the first to steal a flag via a particular daemon.\\r\\nBy solving a daemon, not only will the team be awarded with points, the team will also be awarded with a Weaponized SCADA exploit that can be launched against a rival team. There will be a total of ten (10) daemons all together, hence ten (10) weaponized SCADA exploits available for each team to acquire. No extra points will be awarded to the team that launches it, however monetary damage will be inflicted against the target team. If a team’s money reaches zero (0), the team will automatically be kicked out of the competition. Keep in mind that each weaponized SCADA exploit may only be used once. Depending on the difficulty of exploitation of the daemon, each weaponized SCADA exploit will carry a different damage rating.\\r\\nAs mentioned earlier, Fallout Apocalypse will feature a Black Market where teams can conveniently purchase items from the shop and also trade exploits amongst each other.  Items such as protection and countermeasures can be purchased while on the other hand, teams who wish to auction off their exploits can do so via a broker (The CTF Crew). The owner of the exploit will inform the broker of starting price and the broker will auction it off to the highest bidder. The profit obtained from the purchase will be added to the seller’s pot of gold (total points).\\r\\nAt the end of the competition, the team with the most money (total points) will be crowned as the winner. Hence, teams will need to make sure their daemons are up and running and also harvest flags from time to time for more points. Flags are changed periodically to allow teams to obtain more points by harvesting flags. The CTF network will be isolated from the rest of the conference network, and we will NOT provide Internet on the CTF network. However, you are free to use the HITB conference wireless network.\",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":2,\"public_votable\":false,\"duration\":{\"hours\":9,\"days\":3},\"url\":\"http://conference.hitb.org/hitbsecconf2014kul/capture-the-flag/\",\"ctf_id\":34,\"finish\":\"2012-10-11T14:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-10-08T05:00:00+00:00\",\"location\":\"Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\",\"onsite\":true,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"HitbSecConf CTF (Kuala Lumpur) 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/39/\"}}'),(51,44,'GreHack CTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Grenoble, France\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/52/\",\"title\":\"GreHack CTF 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"\",\"finish\":\"2012-10-20T02:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-10-19T16:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":42,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":10,\"days\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://www.grehack.fr/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[],\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":0,\"participants\":0,\"id\":52}}'),(52,41,'Ruxcon CTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":47,\"participants\":0,\"weight\":0,\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[],\"format_id\":2,\"url\":\"http://www.ruxcon.org.au/\",\"duration\":{\"days\":0,\"hours\":6},\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":39,\"start\":\"2012-10-20T09:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-10-20T15:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"Ruxcon CTF 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/47/\",\"location\":\"Melbourne, Australia\",\"onsite\":true}}'),(53,8,'Hack.lu CTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctf_id\":8,\"start\":\"2012-10-23T07:00:00+00:00\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/38/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"onsite\":false,\"weight\":70,\"location\":\"Luxembourg / On-line\",\"finish\":\"2012-10-25T07:00:00+00:00\",\"logo\":\"\",\"description\":\"The 2012\'s CTF will at hack.lu again be held by FluxFingers, the CTF Team of Ruhr-Universität Bochum (Germany).\\r\\n\\r\\nLast year\'s positive feedback has convinced FluxFingers to host another challenge-style CTF competition at hack.lu. It is safe to assume that the usual topics are included: crypto, reversing, forensic and web security. \",\"url\":\"http://hack.lu/\",\"id\":38,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":false,\"participants\":40,\"title\":\"Hack.lu CTF 2012\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":551,\"name\":\"FluxFingers\"}],\"is_votable_now\":false,\"live_feed\":\"\"},\"url\":\"https://ctf.fluxfingers.net/2012\"}'),(54,38,'Hackfest 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"==== SATURDAY NIGHT CHALLENGE ====\\r\\n\\r\\n-=Registration=-\\r\\nhttp://www.hackfest.ca/en/hacking-games/saturday\\r\\n\\r\\n-=VPN for participant out of the province of Quebec=-\\r\\nVPN was reported.\\r\\n\\r\\n-=Challenges=-\\r\\nSaturday’s event will be the classic CTF format. The enphasis is on the way teams are versatile and how they use their skills. Like in the friday night, points are gained by exploiting vulnerabilities. Challenges generally have the following caracteristics:\\r\\n\\r\\nPretty easy to understand\\r\\nDifficulty ranges from easy to hard\\r\\nVariety to please everyone\\r\\nHere are the challenges of this year. (Note that they’re subject to change):\\r\\n\\r\\n-Web-\\r\\n\\r\\nYour goal is to find and exploit vulnerabilities exposed by various websites. Your analytical skills will be solicited more than ever in this edition. You’ll need to read between the lines of code.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe challenges of the past years could serve as warm-up.\\r\\n\\r\\nhttp://www.hackfest.ca/hacking-games/anciens-jeux\\r\\n\\r\\n-Phony app-\\r\\n\\r\\nAndroid, Windows Phone, iOS… Is there such a thing as mobile security?\\r\\n\\r\\n-Exploits-\\r\\n\\r\\nNMAP is a pretty good tool, but unfortunately it won’t get you root on the box.\\r\\n\\r\\n-Crypto-\\r\\n\\r\\nHow are you supposed to communicate with the real world… in plain text? Welcome to 2012.\\r\\n\\r\\n-Crackme-\\r\\n\\r\\nBring some computation power to crack those hashes you will find on your way to salvation. This track will be integrated into others.\\r\\n\\r\\n-Trivia-\\r\\n\\r\\nIRC quizz-style trivia led by our famous host, ChuckNorris. Questions will be related to anything ITsec, hacking, scene, history, etc. They will range from general knowledge to specific technical questions\\r\\n\\r\\n-Lock Picking-\\r\\n\\r\\nAll details here: http://www.hackfest.ca/en/hacking-games/lock-picking-pro-clef\\r\\n\\r\\n-Data mining-\\r\\n\\r\\nYou’re gonna stumble on some informations, find out what to do with them or find out about different ways to present information.\\r\\n\\r\\nRegistration: You must register by e-mail before 6:00 PM, eastern time, to have your team on the scoreboard\\r\\n \\r\\n \\r\\n \\r\\n==== FRIDAY NIGHT CHALLENGE ====\\r\\n\\r\\n-=Registration=-\\r\\nhttp://www.hackfest.ca/en/hacking-games/friday\\r\\n\\r\\n-=Scenario=-\\r\\nIn 2010, two (2) pharmaceutical companies went head-to-head in a winner take all cyber-battle to obtain a lucrative contract. The winner would surely be considered as the world leader in pharmaceutical products, making investors rich beyond belief.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis year, Hackfest is presenting a similar scenario, only this time a multitude of corporate entities will be battling it out in what is today’s most hostile environment: The Internet. Keeping the same model as previous years, teams will not only need to attack, but also defend their respective networks in order to obtain the ultimate prize. Players will be placed in a war mood and in a realistic environment. Players should be see:\\r\\n\\r\\n  - An internet simulation\\r\\n  - An anonymity system\\r\\n  - A military base with a SCADA system\\r\\n  - An international bank\\r\\n  - Multiple operating system such as: CentOS, Windows and Debian\\r\\n  - IPv6 telephony systems\\r\\n  - And More…\\r\\n\\r\\nPlayers can already get ready for the games! See details on the web site.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor more information about the hackfest “Red / Blue” contest , please see the last two years editions pages.\",\"format_id\":2,\"url\":\"http://www.hackfest.ca/\",\"duration\":{\"days\":0,\"hours\":8},\"public_votable\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":4852,\"name\":\"Hackfest Crew\"}],\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2012-11-03T07:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-11-02T23:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":37,\"location\":\"Quebec, Canada\",\"onsite\":true,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/44/\",\"title\":\"Hackfest 2012\",\"weight\":20,\"id\":44,\"participants\":12,\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/favicon-64x64.png\",\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\"}}'),(55,28,'Power of XX 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/55/\",\"title\":\"Power of XX 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Seoul, Republic of Korea\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-11-08T01:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2012-11-08T09:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":28,\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://www.powerofxx.com/\",\"duration\":{\"days\":0,\"hours\":8},\"public_votable\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"SISS\",\"id\":3263}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"description\":\"The 2nd Power of XX\\r\\n\\r\\n- Date\\r\\n(Qualifying Round) Nov. 3, 2012, 10:00 ~ 20:00\\r\\n(Final Round) Nov. 8, 2012, 10:00 ~ 18:00\\r\\n\\r\\n- Winners\\r\\nThe First | K.Knock (Korea, Kyonggi University)\\r\\nThe Second | puttyputty~<3 (Korea, Sunrin High School)\\r\\nThe Third | Pussycat (Korea, The Catholic University of Korea)\\r\\n\",\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"participants\":0,\"id\":55,\"weight\":0}}'),(56,45,'CSCAMP CTF Quals 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"weight\":10,\"participants\":10,\"id\":53,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"description\":\"http://synapse-labs.com/cscamp/\",\"finish\":\"2012-11-11T06:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2012-11-09T06:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":43,\"url\":\"http://www.cairosecuritycamp.com/ctf/\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"public_votable\":false,\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/53/\",\"title\":\"CSCAMP CTF Quals 2012\",\"live_feed\":\"\"}}'),(57,19,'CSAW CTF Final Round 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"CSAW CTF Organizers\",\"id\":2488}],\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"https://csawctf.poly.edu/\",\"ctf_id\":19,\"finish\":\"2012-11-17T18:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2012-11-15T18:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"Final will be held in Polytechnic Institute of New York University Six MetroTech Center Brooklyn, NY 11201 (<a href=\\\"https://maps.google.com/maps?q=Polytechnic+Institute+of+New+York+University+Six+MetroTech+Center+Brooklyn,+NY+11201&hl=ru&ll=40.695184,-73.986933&spn=0.008069,0.019462&sll=37.0625,-95.677068&sspn=34.534108,79.716797&hnear=Polytechnic+Institute+of+NYU,+6+Metrotech+Center,+Brooklyn,+New+York+11201-3840&t=m&z=16&iwloc=A\\\">map</a>).\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"CSAW CTF Final Round 2012\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/43/\",\"location\":\"NY, USA\",\"onsite\":true,\"id\":43,\"participants\":11,\"weight\":30,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(58,42,'PoliCTF 2012',2012,'{\"ctftime\":{\"title\":\