'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/167/\",\"title\":\"MalCon 2014 Quals\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"start\":\"2014-10-03T16:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2014-10-06T16:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":87,\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":3},\"url\":\"http://ctf.malwareconference.org/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":11347,\"name\":\"MalCon CTF\"}],\"description\":\"Be a part of this inaugural offense-only CTF event! Register for Quals by Thursday October 2, @ 5pm EST (9pm UTC) - http://ctf.malwareconference.org Don\'t you want to play for $1000 and a shiny trophy????? Don\'t you want to be crowned the 1st ever winner of MalCon CTF???? Don\'t you want to be on the beach in Puerto Rico in October???? We are seeking all skill levels, teams can be 1 to 5 players, the CTF designers are active U.S. government pen testers and this CTF reflects what they encounter in the field. The quals round will occur online from 12 noon October 3rd to 12 noon October 6th. Prizes: $1000 and a shiny trophy for 1st place, $500 for 2nd place, and $250 for 3rd place in the final round which will take place on October 30, 2014 at El Conquistador Hotel in Puerto Rico! Email questions to ctf@malwareconference.org - The 1st Annual MalCon CTF is part of the 2014 IEEE Malware Conference and is sponsored by Microsoft. Registration and details: http://ctf.malwareconference.org\\r\\n\\r\\nTop 5 teams from Quals will advance to final round in Puerto Rico on October 30, 2014.\",\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"participants\":33,\"id\":167,\"weight\":5}}'),(158,60,'ASIS CTF Finals 2014',2014,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":147,\"participants\":92,\"weight\":30,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":4140,\"name\":\"ASIS\"}],\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://asis-ctf.ir/\",\"ctf_id\":59,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2014-10-13T06:30:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2014-10-11T06:30:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"ASIS CTF Finals 2014\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/147/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false}}'),(159,32,'HITB2014KUL Capture the Flag: Age of Extinction',2014,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia\",\"title\":\"HITB2014KUL Capture the Flag: Age of Extinction\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/169/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"Overview\\r\\n========================\\r\\n\\r\\nThe objective of the game is for teams (maximum of 3 participants per team) to gain as many points as possible by defending their servers and attacking other teams’ servers. \\r\\n\\r\\nTeams will be given identical pre-configured vmware image of an Linux installation – the root password will not be given to the team. There will be daemons running on the servers. Some daemons are puzzle-based challenges and some contain vulnerabilities such as buffer overflow, format string and so on. \\r\\n\\r\\nThe teams’ objective is to analyze the daemons, find vulnerabilities and write exploits. A working exploit will enable the team to attack other teams\' servers, retrieving the flag associated with each daemon running on the server and thus scoring an offensive point. The ability to keep the daemons running will enable the teams to score a defensive point. \\r\\n\\r\\nScoring\\r\\n========================\\r\\n\\r\\nOffensive Points = Gained by hacking into other team’s server and retrieving their flags.\\r\\n\\r\\nDefensive Points = Gained by keeping your server’s daemons running.\\r\\n\\r\\nChallenge Points = Gained by submit the correct flags for challenges\\r\\n\\r\\nTotal points = offensive points + defensive points + challenge points\\r\\n\\r\\nIn order to score an offensive point, all that a team needs to do is hack into other team’s server, retrieve the flag, and submit it to the score server. In order to get a defensive score, teams must keep their daemons running and accessible by the crew. Flag checks will be done randomly. If a flag check fails, teams will not gain a defensive point. Flags will be reset randomly as well, thus teams are allowed to harvest flags to gain more offensive points.\\r\\n\\r\\nHigher points are given for offensive attacks as opposed to defensive scores. Defensive scores are the same for all daemons while offensive scores vary depending on the complexity level of the exploit needed. The first team able to exploit the daemon will gain a ‘breakthrough point’.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt the end of the competition, the team with highest total points will be the one who rules the world! In case of two different teams having the same points, whichever team is quickest to reach the highest points will be declared the winner. As such, teams are advised to submit the flags as soon as they obtain them.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe CTF network will be isolated from the rest of the conference network and we will NOT provide Internet access on the CTF network. You are free to use the HITB conference wireless network.\",\"ctf_id\":34,\"start\":\"2014-10-15T02:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2014-10-16T10:00:00+00:00\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"nasilemak0\",\"id\":605}],\"duration\":{\"hours\":8,\"days\":1},\"format_id\":2,\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://conference.hitb.org/hitbsecconf2014kul/capture-the-flag/\",\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"\",\"weight\":20,\"participants\":8,\"id\":169}}'),(160,73,'Defcamp CTF Qualification 2014',2014,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/155/\",\"title\":\"Defcamp CTF Qualification 2014\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"D-CTF 2014 Qualifications is the main CTF competition for Defcamp, an international hacking & infosec conference. It’s all about teamwork, eyes wide open and remarkable skills. Every time it spreads the newest security techniques and supports measuring the security skills of the teams. A complete team covering all the main skills is always the best option to get into the finals. In the same time the competition does strengthen both technical and management skills; the leader is coordinating everything, every step from the process making sure that the team is following the line to capture the flag. Everything is doubled with mystery, mathematics and complicated algorithms to make everything even more challenging. Some consider this competition as a game, because originally it was a game that simulate small team combat, based on defending an immobile flag while trying to capture the flag of the other team. D-CTF \'14 Qualifications: http://dctf.defcamp.ro DefCamp Website: http://defcamp.ro\",\"start\":\"2014-10-18T11:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2014-10-20T11:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":73,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://dctf.def.camp/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"CCSIR.org\",\"id\":9831}],\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":5,\"participants\":109,\"id\":155}}'),(161,80,'UConn CyberSEED 2014',2014,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":160,\"participants\":8,\"weight\":5,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"UConn CyberSEED 2014\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/160/\",\"location\":\"Storrs, CT, USA\",\"onsite\":true,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":17638,\"name\":\"UConn CyberSEED\"}],\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":3},\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://www.cyberseed.org/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":85,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2014-10-22T17:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2014-10-20T14:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"The CyberSEED Challenge is sponsored by Comcast Corporation.  The competition is open to teams from high schools, community colleges, or 4-year colleges in the United States.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe software challenge asks students to design a buffer overflow attack and might appeal to students who have good programming skills.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe capture the flag challenge is similar to many existing cybersecurity challenges and should be appropriate for students who have taken basic network or web security classes.\\r\\n\\r\\nTeams should register for the competition by September 26, 2014. Because of limited space, only the first 20 teams will be allowed to compete.\\r\\n\\r\\nEach team that is accepted into the competition will be granted a travel award to help cover travel expenses. The amount depends on the location of the team and the number of team members.\"}}'),(162,8,'Hack.lu CTF 2014',2014,'{\"url\":\"https://ctf.fluxfingers.net/2014\",\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"The hack.lu CTF aims to entertain good teams as well as beginners. Expect a wide variety of carefully designed, beautifully handcrafted and family-friendly challenges!\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is the fifth time the hack.lu CTF is organized by the FluxFingers, the CTF team of the Ruhr-University Bochum (Germany).\\r\\n\\r\\nFor this anniversary expect some surprises like absent netflow and more trolling in the IRC channels. It will be a fun event for the whole family, so drop by and have a beer with us!\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":154,\"url\":\"http://2014.hack.lu/index.php/CaptureTheFlag\",\"participants\":100,\"title\":\"Hack.lu CTF 2014\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"FluxFingers\",\"id\":551}],\"ctf_id\":8,\"start\":\"2014-10-21T08:00:00+00:00\",\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/154/\",\"onsite\":false,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":70,\"location\":\"Luxembourg\",\"finish\":\"2014-10-23T08:00:00+00:00\"}}'),(163,70,'No cON Name CTF Finals 2014',2014,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\