\"days\":0},\"format_id\":2,\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://volgactf.ru/\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"Koibasta\",\"id\":496}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Russia, Samara\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/232/\",\"title\":\"VolgaCTF 2015 Finals\",\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/232/\",\"weight\":0,\"participants\":5,\"id\":232,\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/logo-black.png\",\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\"}}'),(221,103,'STEM CTF: Cyber Challenge 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"STEM CTF: Cyber Challenge 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/216/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"id\":13562,\"name\":\"MITRE Cyber Academy\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://ctf.mitrecyberacademy.org/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":4,\"days\":1},\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":106,\"finish\":\"2015-09-12T23:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-09-11T19:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"In support of STEM outreach, MITRE and (ISC)²® is hosting the annual national Capture the Flag (CTF) competition.High school and undergraduate college students will have the opportunity to compete in cybersecurity challenges to gain real-life experience and win national coverage to make a huge impact. Notable industry and academic experts have partnered together to design rigorous challenges for students to solve. Competing in teams of four, students will gain the necessary tools to compete in the nationwide competition.\\r\\n\\r\\nWinning teams will have the opportunity to receive a college scholarship, vouchers to take the SSCP® Exam, as well as early regard for MITRE’s Industry Partner Cyber Internship program*. *Participation in MITRE’s Cyber Internship program is subject to an interviewing process and based on current business needs.\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":216,\"participants\":80,\"weight\":0}}'),(222,18,'CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/CSAW15LOGO_COLOR.png\",\"id\":227,\"participants\":174,\"weight\":40,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/227/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":2488,\"name\":\"CSAW CTF Organizers\"}],\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"url\":\"https://ctf.isis.poly.edu/\",\"ctf_id\":18,\"start\":\"2015-09-18T22:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-09-20T22:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"description\":\"Students tackle problems in a series of real-world scenarios modeling all sorts of computer security problems where, to succeed, they must demonstrate a profound understanding of the roles and ramifications of cyber security in these situations.\\r\\n\\r\\nBecause the challenges are designed to teach, CTF requires contestants to integrate concepts, develop skills and learn to hack as they go. Undergraduate finalists compete on-site for cash prizes, where their performance is judged by a panel of technical experts.\"}}'),(223,111,'Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 Online Qualifier',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 is an event hosted by Trend Micro, a global leader in security software and solutions with the vision ‘a world safe for exchanging digital information’.<br/><br/>Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 combines online qualifier and on-site final. Top ten teams from the qualifier will automatically qualify for the final, hosted in Tokyo in November 2015.<br/><br/>Challenges include not only orthodox categories such as ‘binary analysis’ and ‘packet analysis’, but also ‘targeted attacks’, ‘virtualisation\', etc., to reflect the current and future business IT environments.<br/><br/>Requirement<br/>- Resident in Asia Pacific and Japan countries and regions (*see official website for more details)<br/>- Adults aged over 20 <br/>- Please note that participants who are from outside Asia Pacific & Japan countries and regions and finished among top ten will not be eligible for participating in the final.<br/><br/>Schedule <br/>Duration: 24hrs<br/>Program: Jeopardy-style<br/>Challenge categories include, in addition to ‘binary’ and ‘packet’, ‘targeted attack’, ‘IoT’, and ‘ICS/SCADA’ planned - 30 challenge, with five in six different categories planned<br/>Language:English (with Japanese support)\",\"ctf_id\":114,\"start\":\"2015-09-26T04:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-09-27T04:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"Trend Micro\",\"id\":16963}],\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":1},\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://www.trendmicro.co.jp/jp/sp/ctf2015_en/index.html\",\"public_votable\":false,\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"title\":\"Trend Micro CTF Asia Pacific & Japan 2015 Online Qualifier\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/230/\",\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/230/\",\"weight\":20,\"participants\":144,\"id\":230,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/tctf2015.png\"}}'),(224,73,'Defcamp CTF Qualification 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"Announcement: We decided to change the dates in order to allow the community to attend at all the events that will happen at the beginning of October. The new dates are:  02 Oct. 2015, 09:00 PM UTC - 4 Oct. 2015, 09:00 AM UTC (36 hours). \\r\\n\\r\\nD-CTF is the traditional Capture the Flag Jeopardy style competition organised during DefCamp international cyber security & hacking conference happening in Bucharest, Romania between 19th and 20th of November. The competition has two phases:\\r\\n - October 3th - 4th, Online Qualification \\r\\n- November 19th - 20th, The Final in Bucharest, Romania with best teams from Online Qualifications \\r\\n\\r\\nBecause challenges are inspired by real life scenarios from day-to-day challenges of industry experts and other CTF players, you have to prove the ability to develop skills and under stress. It will be fun, I promise! :-)\",\"start\":\"2015-10-02T21:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2015-10-04T09:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":73,\"url\":\"http://dctf.def.camp/\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":12},\"public_votable\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"CCSIR.org\",\"id\":9831}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/239/\",\"title\":\"Defcamp CTF Qualification 2015\",\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/239/\",\"weight\":10,\"participants\":138,\"id\":239,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\"}}'),(225,60,'ASIS CTF Finals 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"live_feed\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/223/\",\"title\":\"ASIS CTF Finals 2015\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":false,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"url\":\"http://asis-ctf.ir/\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":4140,\"name\":\"ASIS\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"start\":\"2015-10-10T06:30:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-10-12T06:30:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":59,\"description\":\"\",\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"id\":223,\"participants\":114,\"weight\":40}}'),(226,110,'Hackover CTF 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"participants\":75,\"id\":249,\"weight\":5,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/Invader2015_2.png\",\"ctf_id\":122,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-10-16T18:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-10-18T06:00:00+00:00\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"Cyclopropenylidene\",\"id\":9882}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":12},\"url\":\"https://ctf.hackover.de/\",\"description\":\"Who\\r\\nThis CTF is run by the Hamburg local chapter of the Chaos Computer Club during the Hackover event.\\r\\n\\r\\nIRC\\r\\n#hackover-ctf on irc.hackint.org:9999 (SSL only!).\\r\\n\\r\\nChallenges\\r\\nThe tasks will contain classical categories like binary pwnable, forensics, crypto, reversing, misc etc\\r\\n\\r\\nSSL certificate\\r\\nsha256 fingerprint: 24:95:FC:2C:E5:3E:7F:0B:5E:63:4D:2F:B6:12:68:51:93:EA:42:2D:FB:55:7F:DE:96:89:FF:1C:7D:2A:6A:09\",\"title\":\"Hackover CTF 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/249/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\"}}'),(227,30,'HITCON CTF 2015 Quals',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/logo2-01.jpg\",\"participants\":119,\"id\":245,\"weight\":50,\"title\":\"HITCON CTF 2015 Quals\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/245/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctf_id\":79,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-10-17T02:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-10-18T14:00:00+00:00\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":8299,\"name\":\"HITCON\"}],\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":12},\"url\":\"http://ctf.hitcon.org/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"description\":\"Finally, HITCON will present you “Attack & Defense”!  \\r\\nWe are pleased to announce that the HITCON CTF “Attack & Defense” competition is about to start.\\r\\n\\r\\nTime for qualification is Oct 17 10:00 AM ~ Oct 18 10:00 PM (GMT+8, 36 hours)\\r\\nTop 10 teams will be invited  to HITCON CTF Final in Dec 5-6 (Onsite Attack & Defense in Taipei)       \\r\\n\\r\\n1. Qualification is online jeopardy including reversing, pwnable, crypto, forensic, web, misc...\\r\\n2. We will \\\"partially\\\" support top 10 teams for their flight and accommodation.\\r\\n3. Awards in final:  1st place: $10,000 USD, 2nd place: $5,000 USD, 3rd place: $2,000 USD. Special award fo Top 1 Taiwan team: $1,000 USD\\r\\n4. Online registration will open at Oct 4 3:00 PM. Please keep following our official website: http://ctf.hitcon.org\\r\\n\\r\\nQuals: Online Jeopardy, Oct 17-18, 2015\\r\\nFinal: Attack & Defense, Dec 5-6, 2015 (4 players / team)\\r\\n\\r\\nCurrently 2015 HITCON CTF Qualifying Contests:\\r\\nThe champions of the following contests will pre-qualify directly for the final in December and do not need to participate in the preliminary in 17th October.\\r\\n1. TrendMicro CTF Japan\\r\\n2. AIS3 Challenges\\r\\n3. CTCTF 2015\\r\\n\"}}'),(228,8,'Hack.lu CTF 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"weight\":70,\"participants\":126,\"id\":244,\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"title\":\"Hack.lu CTF 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/244/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"This year\'s CTF will take place at https://school.fluxfingers.net\\r\\nRegistration is open!\\r\\n\\r\\nOfficial CTF IRC Channel: #fluxfingers@freenode\",\"ctf_id\":8,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2015-10-22T08:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2015-10-20T08:00:00+00:00\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"FluxFingers\",\"id\":551}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://hack.lu/\"}}'),(229,119,'EKOPARTY CTF 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/logo_ekoparty_1.png\",\"id\":247,\"participants\":81,\"weight\":40,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"EKOPARTY CTF 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/247/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":321,\"name\":\"NULL Life\"}],\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":8,\"days\":1},\"url\":\"https://ctf.ekoparty.org/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":121,\"finish\":\"2015-10-23T20:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-10-22T12:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"The EKOPARTY CTF 2015 is an IT security competition targeted for all the enthusiasts and computer security professionals out there trying to put their skills to the test!\"}}'),(230,39,'2nd Annual MalCon CTF',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Fajardo, Puerto Rico\",\"title\":\"2nd Annual MalCon CTF\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/261/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"The 2nd MalCon CTF is designed to reflect real life scenarios faced by security professionals when deployed in the field. In this offense-only event, the team’s job is to penetrate several layers of a system and collect flags for points along the way. Our tech team consists of active security professionals with several years’ experience in on and off site penetration testing. Their experience, expertise, and know how are leveraged to create a fun CTF that is technically challenging and realistic. When: October 22nd 2015, 9am – 6pm EST Where: El Conquistador Hotel Fajardo Puerto Rico, and remote. Registration: $250 play onsite (per 4 member team), $150 play remote. Onsite registration includes breakfast, lunch, and snacks. Register at: http://www.malwareconference.org questions: ctf@malwareconference.org The 2nd Annual MalCon CTF is part of the 2015 IEEE Malware Conference and is sponsored by Microsoft.\",\"ctf_id\":87,\"finish\":\"2015-10-22T22:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-10-22T13:00:00+00:00\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":11347,\"name\":\"MalCon CTF\"}],\"url\":\"http://malwareconference.org/index.php/2nd-annual-capture-the-flag-ctf-competition\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":9,\"days\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"weight\":0,\"participants\":0,\"id\":261}}'),(231,121,'WhiteHat Grand Prix – Qualification Round 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"organizers\":[{\"id\":16789,\"name\":\"BTeam\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"public_votable\":false,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":0},\"url\":\"http://whitehatvn.com/\",\"ctf_id\":124,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2015-10-24T02:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-10-25T02:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"WhiteHat Grand Prix, a Capture The Flag competition, is held annually by WhiteHatVN.com, leading cyber security forum in Vietnam. Challenges in the competition are created by BTeam, VNSecurity \\r\\n\\r\\nThe Qualification Round is held continuously in 24 hours, from 24th to 25th October, online at WhiteHatVN.com. On December 19, top 10 teams of the Qualification Round will participate in the Final Round in the format of Attack/Defense onsite in Hanoi, Vietnam. The Final Round will last for 8 hours continuously. \\r\\n\\r\\nAbout Sponsor: Bkav is Technology Corporation, operating in the field of network security, software, e-Government; manufacturer of smart electronic devices and smartphone, as well as a supplier of Cloud Computing service. \\r\\n\\r\\nFollow us: https://twitter.com/WhiteHatVN\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"WhiteHat Grand Prix – Qualification Round 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/246/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"id\":246,\"participants\":73,\"weight\":20,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(232,117,'TUM CTF Teaser',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":238,\"participants\":65,\"weight\":20,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":585,\"name\":\"H4x0rPsch0rr\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://ctf.hxp.io/\",\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":120,\"start\":\"2015-10-24T12:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2015-10-25T12:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"The TUM CTF Teaser will be the first CTF held by H4x0rPsch0rr, the team of the TU München. The Teaser will last for 24 hours, jeopardy style, five categories.\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"TUM CTF Teaser\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/238/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false}}'),(233,80,'UConn CyberSEED 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/240/\",\"title\":\"UConn CyberSEED 2015\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Storrs, CT, USA\",\"finish\":\"2015-10-30T22:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2015-10-29T12:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"ctf_id\":85,\"duration\":{\"hours\":10,\"days\":1},\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://www.cyberseed.org/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"UConn CyberSEED\",\"id\":17638}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"description\":\"The Capture the Flag Challenge is an immersive, interactive competition that uses realistic IT infrastructure to simulate the current threat landscape. Designed for many levels of technical skill and experience, the competition puts participants in the hackers’ shoes to understand their technology and thought processes. Sponsored by Symantec, the Capture the Flag Challenge asks teams to attack a virtual corporate network in a series of progressively more difficult penetration exercises. The competition is intended for high-school and college teams. Participants have the opportunity to: Sharpen security skills such as forensics, penetration testing, and more Expand security awareness Learn and try new techniques Compete against their peers for prizes and bragging rights Comcast is providing travel support for teams to attend.\",\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"participants\":28,\"id\":240,\"weight\":5}}'),(234,104,'School CTF 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"title\":\"School CTF 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/254/\",\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/254/\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctf_id\":107,\"start\":\"2015-11-04T06:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2015-11-04T11:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"id\":557,\"name\":\"SiBears\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"duration\":{\"days\":0,\"hours\":5},\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"http://school-ctf.org/\",\"description\":\"School CTF is the computer security competition for school pupils that is hosted by the SiBears team annually since 2010. School CTF traditionally takes place in autumn. Any team is welcome, not just that comprised of school pupils. The ratings are calculated separately for school teams and for all teams.\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/new-bear-lg.png\",\"participants\":79,\"id\":254,\"weight\":0}}'),(235,126,'Belluminar 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"Belluminar is the hacking contest of POC. Belluminar is from ‘Bellum’(war in Latin) and ‘seminar’. It is not a mere hacking contest but a kind of festival consisted of contest & seminar. This year, only invited teams can join Belluminar. Each team can show its ability to attack what other teams want to protect and can defend what others want to attack. Belluminar is composed of a CTF(1st day or half day more) and a seminar for the solution about challenges(2nd day). \",\"organizers\":[],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":2,\"days\":1},\"url\":\"http://www.powerofcommunity.net/belluminar.htm\",\"public_votable\":false,\"ctf_id\":128,\"finish\":\"2015-11-06T04:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2015-11-05T02:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"location\":\"Seoul, Republic of Korea\",\"onsite\":true,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"Belluminar 2015\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/269/\",\"weight\":0,\"id\":269,\"participants\":0,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(236,123,'g0s CTF 2015',2015,'{\"ctftime\":{\"weight\":5,\"participants\":7,\"id\":259,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"description\":\"The enemy is about to unleash a chemical weapon and you are the only hope of Planet Earth! Race against time to deactivate the weapon by your hacking skills and save the planet. The capture the flag contest will be held on 5th and 6th November and shall consist of 10 different technical challenges. The contestant who completes all the levels fastest than other participants will be awarded the prize.\\r\\n\\r\\nEdit: The event will be held on-site at New Delhi, 