p://ABCTF.xyz/\",\"ctf_id\":153,\"start\":\"2016-07-15T18:23:26+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2016-07-22T18:23:25+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"description\":\"High school level CTF, made by HighSchoolers. Everyone and anyone can play but only k-12 are eligible for prizes!\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"ABCTF 2016\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/333/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"id\":333,\"participants\":86,\"weight\":0,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(311,152,'LabyREnth 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"Overview - http://labyrenth.com/1_d0nt_kn0w_wh3r3_1m_g01ng.html\\r\\nOfficial Rules - http://labyrenth.com/8ut_1_pr0m1s3.html\\r\\n\",\"ctf_id\":156,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-08-14T23:59:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-07-15T23:59:00+00:00\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":27408,\"name\":\"Palo Alto Networks\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://labyrenth.com/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":30},\"public_votable\":false,\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"title\":\"LabyREnth 2016\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/338/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"weight\":0,\"participants\":60,\"id\":338,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(312,111,'Trend Micro CTF 2016 Online Qualifier',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"id\":340,\"participants\":79,\"weight\":20.9,\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/340/\",\"title\":\"Trend Micro CTF 2016 Online Qualifier\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/340/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"Trend Micro\",\"id\":16963}],\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":true,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":1},\"url\":\"http://www.trendmicro.co.jp/jp/sp/ctf2016_en/index.html\",\"ctf_id\":114,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-07-31T04:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-07-30T04:00:00+00:00\",\"description\":\"Overview: IT environments are shifting from traditional physical environments towards virtualisation, cloud and IoT (Internet of Things). In addition to traditional business environments, various systems including industrial control systems and smart devices are connetcted to the internet. On the other hand, with no boundaries on the internet, cyber attacks are becoming increasingly damaging and critical.\\r\\n\\r\\nTrend Micro CTF is a CTF event hosted by Trend Micro, a global leader in security software and solutions with the vision \'a world safe for exchanging digital information’.\\r\\n\\r\\nTrend Micro CTF 2016 combines online qualifier and on-site final. Top ten teams from the qualifier will automatically qualify for the final, hosted in Tokyo in November 2016.\\r\\n\\r\\nChallenges include not only orthodox categories such as ‘binary analysis’ and ‘packet analysis’, but also ‘targeted attacks’, ‘IoT’ and ‘SCADA’ to reflect the current and future business IT environments.\\r\\n\\r\\nOnline Qualifier Dates: July 30 2016 to July 31 2016 (JST)\\r\\nStart Time:13:00 (JST, or 4:00 UTC), July 30 2016\\r\\nRequirements: Adults aged over 20\\r\\nProgram: Jeopardy-style\\r\\nChallenge categories include, in addition to ‘binary’ and ‘packet’, ‘targeted attack’, ‘IoT’, and ‘ICS/SCADA’ planned (categories are subject to change)\\r\\nLanguage: English\\r\\nVenue: Online (requires internet connection)\\r\\nMore details including game duration will be announced soon\"}}'),(313,81,'OpenCTF 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"participants\":8,\"id\":343,\"weight\":22,\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/343/\",\"title\":\"OpenCTF 2016\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Las Vegas, United States\",\"finish\":\"2016-08-07T04:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2016-08-05T17:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":81,\"url\":\"http://openctf.com/\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":11},\"public_votable\":true,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"vand\",\"id\":359}],\"description\":\"In OpenCTF, teams compete to solve hacking challenges in a wide variety of categories, including web, forensics, programming, cryptography and reverse engineering. There will be challenges for all skill levels. If you\'ve never played in a capture the flag contest before, please feel free to stop by anyway - we\'ll explain how it works and do what we can to set set up with a team. Optional preregistration, as well as some tips on what to bring and how to prepare, can be found at OpenCTF.com.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou must have at least one team member attending DEFCON to play OpenCTF. Arrangements for non-local players are none of our business or concern.\\r\\n\\r\\nOfficial website for Pre-Reg is here: http://openctf.com\\r\\ntwitter for updates and hints: @open_ctf\\r\\nOpenCTF on the <a href=\\\"https://forum.defcon.org/forum/defcon/dc24-official-unofficial-parties-social-gatherings-events-contests/dc24-official-and-unofficial-contests/openctf-open-capture-the-flag-aa\\\">DEFCON forums</a>.\\r\\n\"}}'),(314,2,'DEF CON CTF 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":344,\"participants\":0,\"weight\":80,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"format_id\":2,\"url\":\"http://defcon.org/\",\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":3},\"public_votable\":true,\"organizers\":[{\"id\":9811,\"name\":\"Legitimate Business Syndicate\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Prequalified\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-08-07T21:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-08-05T18:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":2,\"description\":\"\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/344/\",\"title\":\"DEF CON CTF 2016\",\"location\":\"Las Vegas, United States\",\"onsite\":true}}'),(315,146,'IceCTF 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"weight\":0,\"id\":319,\"participants\":141,\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/319/\",\"title\":\"IceCTF 2016\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/319/\",\"description\":\"IceCTF is a computer security contest targeted at anyone with an interest in computer science. The game consists of a series of challenges where participants must reverse engineer, break, hack, decrypt, or do whatever it takes to solve the challenge. The challenges are all set up with the intent of being hacked, making it a great way to get some hands-on experience. IceCTF is designed to accommodate both novice and advanced players alike. Many challenges will guide you to the right resources. As long as you\'re willing to learn and do a little research, most challenges should be within reach. \",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"cRUcible\",\"id\":18421}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":14,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"https://icec.tf/\",\"ctf_id\":150,\"start\":\"2016-08-12T16:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2016-08-26T16:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false}}'),(316,78,'Hackcon 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"With challenges aiming to test skills in the areas of scripting, exploiting web vulnerabilities, reversing and more, Hackcon \'16 is a capture-the-flag style software and web security event which will be held online.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt\'s a team event, upto 4 members allowed, lone wolves also welcome.\\r\\n\\r\\nCross-college/Cross-school/Non-Academic teams allowed.\\r\\n\\r\\nEvent Registration at hackcon.in\",\"start\":\"2016-08-19T14:30:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-08-20T18:29:59+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":115,\"public_votable\":true,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":3},\"url\":\"http://hackcon.in/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"d4rkc0de\",\"id\":15154}],\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/341/\",\"title\":\"Hackcon 2016\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"weight\":16.47,\"participants\":120,\"id\":341,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\"}}'),(317,154,'BioTerra CTF 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"Germanys biggest esoteric fair now has a CTF as well. The CTF is jeopardy styled and has all kinds of tasks. It starts 2016-08-20 20:08 UTC and ends 2016-08-21 21:08 UTC.\\r\\n\\r\\nRegistration is open: https://scoreboard.bioterra.xyz/signup\",\"ctf_id\":159,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-08-21T21:08:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-08-20T20:08:00+00:00\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":27880,\"name\":\"BioTerra\"}],\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"https://bioterra.xyz/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":1,\"days\":1},\"public_votable\":true,\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"title\":\"BioTerra CTF 2016\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/350/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"weight\":22,\"participants\":44,\"id\":350,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/bioterra.png\"}}'),(318,62,'Facebook Capture The Flag 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":5,\"participants\":14,\"id\":346,\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Singapore\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/346/\",\"title\":\"Facebook Capture The Flag 2016\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"Registration form at http://gsec.hitb.org/sg2016/facebook-capture-the-flag/ (limited to 2 teams per organization) Overview The objective of the game is for teams (team size of 2 – 4 participants per team) to gain as many points as possible by solving challenges. This is a jeopardy -style CTF with multiple categories of challenges, including: reverse engineering, exploitation, forensics, network analysis, etc. The teams’ objective is to solve the challenges to score as many points as possible. The game will run for 18 hours over the 2 days of the conference (25th & 26th August), 9 hours per day. Scoring At the end of the competition, the team with highest total points will be the winner! In the case of two different teams having the same points, whichever team was quickest to reach the highest points will be declared the winner. As such, teams are advised to submit the flags as soon as they obtain them. \",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2016-08-25T02:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2016-08-26T11:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":61,\"url\":\"http://gsec.hitb.org/sg2016/facebook-capture-the-flag/\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"hours\":9,\"days\":1},\"public_votable\":false,\"organizers\":[{\"id\":2404,\"name\":\"nasilemak\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\"}}'),(319,153,'CTF(x) 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"live_feed\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/348/\",\"title\":\"CTF(x) 2016\",\"description\":\"A beginner level CTF targeted towards high school students. However, anyone is welcome to participate. There are no prizes besides the satisfaction that comes with winning :)\",\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://ctfx.io/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"public_votable\":false,\"restrictions\":\"High-school\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":27453,\"name\":\"CTF(x) Team\"}],\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-08-28T20:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-08-26T20:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":158,\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":0,\"id\":348,\"participants\":71}}'),(320,112,'Tokyo Westerns/MMA CTF 2nd 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"weight\":55.12,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"onsite\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-09-05T00:00:00+00:00\",\"location\":\"\",\"start\":\"2016-09-03T00:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":116,\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/336/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":true,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"title\":\"Tokyo Westerns/MMA CTF 2nd 2016\",\"participants\":141,\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"TokyoWesterns\",\"id\":12599}],\"live_feed\":\"\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"logo\":\"\",\"description\":\"Tokyo Westerns/MMA CTF is a security competition hosted by MMA and Tokyo Westerns. This is the successor of MMA CTF.\",\"url\":\"https://tokyowesterns.github.io/ctf2016/\",\"id\":336},\"download_link\":\"https://github.com/tokyowesterns/twctf-2016-problems\"}'),(321,60,'ASIS CTF Finals 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/327/\",\"title\":\"ASIS CTF Finals 2016\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-09-11T17:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-09-09T17:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":59,\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":true,\"url\":\"http://asis-ctf.ir/\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":4140,\"name\":\"ASIS\"}],\"description\":\"ASIS CTF Final 2016 is open for everyone, and you can register, submit flags, get score and especially CTFTime points, \\r\\nBut Bitcoins will only be awarded to top 3 teams in Finals that are also chosen in ASIS 2016 Qualification round! \\r\\nRead more at: https://asis-ctf.ir/rules/\",\"logo\":\"\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"participants\":119,\"id\":327,\"weight\":57.34}}'),(322,108,'WhiteHat Contest 12',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"participants\":51,\"id\":357,\"weight\":20,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\",\"ctf_id\":112,\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-09-11T02:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-09-10T02:00:00+00:00\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"BTeam\",\"id\":16789}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":true,\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":1},\"url\":\"https://wargame.whitehat.vn/\",\"description\":\"WhiteHat Contest, a Capture The Flag contest, is held periodically by WhiteHat.vn, leading cyber security forum in Vietnam. WhiteHat Contest 12th will be the third Contest to be introduced to the information security community worldwide. WhiteHat Contest is based on WhiteHat Wargame system - the environment allowing cyber security enthusiasts to practice CTF games. WhiteHat.vn is Vietnam’s leading forum on cyber security, where the cyber security research community can exchange expertise, professional ethics as well as legal issues involved. WhiteHat.vn is favorable environment which encourages and promotes cyber security enthusiasts to study and research in judicious orientation to become white hat hackers. These hackers then have high availability in dealing with cyber security incidents. \\r\\nBkav is Technology Corporation, operating in the field of network cyber security, software, e-Government; manufacturer of smart electronic devices and smartphone, as well as a supplier of Cloud Computing service.\\r\\n\\r\\nRegister: https://wargame.whitehat.vn/Account/Register\\r\\n\\r\\nSupport channel: IRC: http://webchat.freenode.net/, channel: whitehatcontest \",\"title\":\"WhiteHat Contest 12\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/357/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\"}}'),(323,54,'VolgaCTF 2016 Finals',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"weight\":10,\"participants\":5,\"id\":328,\"format\":\"Attack-Defense\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/logo-social-yellow.png\",\"description\":\"\",\"ctf_id\":53,\"finish\":\"2016-09-15T15:00:00+00:00\",\"start\":\"2016-09-15T06:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"VolgaCTF.org\",\"id\":27094}],\"format_id\":2,\"duration\":{\"hours\":9,\"days\":0},\"public_votable\":false,\"url\":\"https://volgactf.ru/\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Samara, Russian Federation\",\"title\":\"VolgaCTF 2016 Finals\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/328/\",\"live_feed\":\"https://ctftime.org/live/328/\"}}'),(324,61,'BSides Colombia CTF',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"ctf_id\":60,\"start\":\"2016-09-16T16:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"finish\":\"2016-09-17T16:00:00+00:00\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"HackLab Medellín\",\"id\":27884}],\"duration\":{\"days\":1,\"hours\":0},\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://www.bsidesco.org/\",\"public_votable\":false,\"description\":\"This will be a CTF during event Bsides Colombia 2016 (third edition), We hope to have a good time solving problems related to computer security.\\r\\n\",\"title\":\"BSides Colombia CTF\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/349/\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"onsite\":true,\"location\":\"Medellín, Colombia\",\"participants\":6,\"id\":349,\"weight\":0,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"\"}}'),(325,103,'STEM CTF: Cyber Challenge 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"onsite\":false,\"location\":\"\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/330/\",\"title\":\"STEM CTF: Cyber Challenge 2016\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"description\":\"In support of STEM outreach, MITRE and our partners are hosting the sixth annual national Capture the Flag (CTF) competition.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis CTF competition aims to encourage and promote interest in cybersecurity. United States-based High school and undergraduate college students will have the opportunity to compete in cybersecurity challenges to gain real-life experience and win national coverage to make a huge impact on our cyber talent pipelines.\\r\\n\\r\\nLearn: Fundamental cyber knowledge by using online resources from MITRE, (ISC)2® and other publicly available reputable sources.\\r\\n\\r\\nUnderstand: Binary exploitation and reversing, web exploitation, computer/network forensics, cryptography, critical infrastructure protection/exploitation and more!\\r\\nPractice: Using Web resources and training challenges powered by the MITRE Cyber Academy.\\r\\n\\r\\nCompete: Against students in high school and undergraduate universities across the nation.\\r\\n\\r\\nWin: College scholarships and priority consideration for a cyber internship.\\r\\n\\r\\nNotable industry and academic experts have partnered together to design rigorous challenges for students to solve. Participating in teams of four or five, students will gain valuable experience, skills and tools throughout this nationwide competition.\",\"finish\":\"2016-09-17T17:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"start\":\"2016-09-16T17:00:00+00:00\",\"ctf_id\":106,\"format_id\":1,\"url\":\"http://ctf.mitrecyberacademy.org/\",\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":1},\"public_votable\":false,\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"name\":\"MITRE Cyber Academy\",\"id\":13562}],\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/7783301.png\",\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"weight\":0,\"participants\":82,\"id\":330}}'),(326,18,'CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2016',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"id\":347,\"participants\":122,\"weight\":24.6,\"format\":\"Jeopardy\",\"logo\":\"https://ctftime.org/media/events/Screen_Shot_2016-08-04_at_2.33.23_PM.png\",\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":2488,\"name\":\"CSAW CTF Organizers\"}],\"duration\":{\"hours\":0,\"days\":2},\"format_id\":1,\"public_votable\":true,\"url\":\"https://ctf.csaw.io/\",\"ctf_id\":18,\"start\":\"2016-09-16T23:00:00+00:00\",\"finish\":\"2016-09-18T23:00:00+00:00\",\"is_votable_now\":false,\"description\":\"Students tackle problems in a series of real-world scenarios modeling all sorts of computer security problems where, to succeed, they must demonstrate a profound understanding of the roles and ramifications of cyber security in these situations.\\r\\n\\r\\nBecause the challenges are designed to teach, CTF requires contestants to integrate concepts, develop skills and learn to hack as they go. Undergraduate finalists compete on-site for cash prizes, where their performance is judged by a panel of technical experts.\",\"live_feed\":\"\",\"title\":\"CSAW CTF Qualification Round 2016\",\"ctftime_url\":\"https://ctftime.org/event/347/\",\"location\":\"\",\"onsite\":false}}'),(327,159,'M*CTF 2016 Quals',2016,'{\"ctftime\":{\"description\":\"The competition is open to teams all over the world\\r\\nBut only the top 10 teams from Moscow\'s universities will play in  M*CTF 2016 Final\\r\\n\\r\\nfor more information follow our twitter\\r\\nhttps://twitter.com/mctf_2016\",\"organizers\":[{\"id\":29974,\"name\":\"M*CTF-team\"}],\"restrictions\":\"Open\",\"format_id\":1,\"duration\":{\"days\":2,\"hours\":0},\"public_votable\":true,\"url\":\"http://mctf.aciso.ru/\",\"ctf_id\":164,\"is_vota